				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Apparently you're not disabling rendering before writing the new data to the PPU. You absolutely can't access VRAM while the PPU is rendering, if you try you'll get visual glitches and corrupted VRAM.<br /><br />This is why we can only do visual updates (sprite DMA, pallette updates, small NT changes, etc.) during vblank, a time during which the PPU is not rendering images. For big updates, such as a whole NT, the vblank period isn't enough, so you have to completely disable background and sprite rendering (using register $2001) in order to have free access to VRAM. When you're done transferring the data, you can turn rendering back on.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
