					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">If you ever plan on implementing scrolling, background animations and the like, then yeah, it makes sense to start thinking of a flexible VRAM update system that makes use of the vblank time. If you prefer to start simple, turning rendering off between screens is conceptually simpler, and even people who have more advanced VRAM management may still prefer to turn rendering off during screen transitions and have unlimited VRAM access in order to simplify and speed up larger updates, that may need to replace not only name tables, but also pattern tables.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

