				<table width="100%" cellspacing="5">
				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Best to only toggle it during NMI, yes.<br /><br />Turning off rendering at the wrong time during rendering can cause sprites to be wrong during the next frame in which rendering is enabled again.<br /><br />Turning on rendering during the would-be-active portion will most likely cause the contents of the screen to be wrong for the remainder of that frame.</div>

					<br clear="all" /><br />

						<table width="100%" cellspacing="0">
						<tr valign="middle">
